node.text:
Aurora Borealis... We’ve been dreaming about this one since the beginning of Cercle. We’ll be hosting a very special live performance in Finland, up in the Arctic Circle scheduled on September 7th at 11pm local time (will probably change due to the unpredictability of the auroras so stay alert, read below)

Such an extraordinary place deserved a very special performance…
We are more than honored to welcome the very talented pianist @sofianepamart for an exclusive concert under the northern lights... No controllers or drum machines this time, just the artist and the pure sound of his piano. 

Not only is it a huge technical and human challenge, but doing a show under the northern lights is mostly a big step into the unknown. Many conditions are needed for this phenomenon to happen, and even if we’ll spend an entire week hunting alongside an aurora hunter, we might not even have the chance to see an aurora... So, let’s hope for the best!

Please note that due to these uncertain conditions, the live’s schedule might change or even not happen at all (we will update the Facebook event if needed, and we’ll share our adventures and updates in our stories, so keep an eye open!) 
Otherwise, the livestream will be available on Facebook and Twitch! 

Thank you @ourfinland for this incredible opportunity, and may the hunt begin! 

📸 @allaboutlapland

More than 2 years of discussion to finally receive this amazing person and artist @monolinkmusic from a place that only exist in dreams and movies… Gaathafushi Island, from @wmaldives and @whotels ! 

Doing a show from a desert island was way more difficult than we expected, and at some point during the day of the live we thought that we couldn’t make it, we faced a terrible weather forecast and technical difficulties beyond reason.. 

So when we see the result, we’re so thrilled! 

We hope you’ll like it, it’s a really special one!

Track ID: Turning Away - Monolink (out on all platforms)

node.text:
Nope, you’re not dreaming 😍

Next Monday July 26th we’re teaming up with @whotels to bring our shared passion of music to the untouched paradise of Gaathafushi Island, @wmaldives, with the one and only @monolinkmusic.
We have been waiting for a long time to bring such a unique artist to this incredible tropical playground in the Maldives.

We’ll travel during monsoon so meteorological conditions are unsure, and the livestream schedule might change. If we face heavy rain we might not even be able to shoot... but Cercle is all about adventure, so let’s live another one!

For those who aren’t the waiting kind... Monolink - Turning Away, is now out on Cercle Records! (Link in bio)

This show without audience will be broadcasted live on Facebook, Twitch and Oculus!

Also thanks to @visitmaldives for inviting us to paradise, this one is gonna be magical ✨

#WMaldives
 📸 Kathryn Flexner

Malta here we come again🔥

Next Monday July 12th, we’ll have the pleasure to receive the gifted @anfisaletyago at the Saluting Battery, Malta. 

Its cannons directly facing Fort St. Angelo, the Saluting Battery is located on one of the best vantage points of the city, overlooking the beautiful Grand Harbour. 
Built around 1566, the battery is as old as the City itself. If it once had an important defensive role, it is nowadays used for ceremonial artillery firings, including daily gun salutes.  
Due to the pandemic, this show in partnership with @visitmalta will be held without an audience. 

But the livestream will be available on Facebook, Twitch and Oculus!  Thanks to our local promoter @youblankme!

We mostly live broadcast our shows during sunsets, but for this one, we decided to plan it for the sunrise, because the east terrace would have been in the shadows during sunset but also because @be_svendsen’s music is like a calm & magical morning.

This set will endure the damages of time, as it’s as timeless as the magnificent statues of Mount Nemrut..

This one is going to be magical! 

Next Monday June 14th we’ll be live from another heritage site listed by UNESCO: Mount Nemrut, one of the highest peaks of the eastern Taurus Mountains, Türkiye. We will receive @be_svendsen for an exclusive performance, broadcasted live from the east terrace among the remains of the imperial cult of Commagene. 

This fascinating landscape was once a monumental tumulus built for King Antiochus 1st, with colossal statues representing various divinities and the King himself. These massive sculptures were built in the 1st century B.C., reached 10 meters and weighed 6 tons. A unique landscape, enhanced each day by incredible sunsets and sunrises. 

Recent research revealed that Mount Nemrut’s cavities might contain the King’s tomb, still undiscovered...
